This paper is about improving the quality of Neural Machine Translation models, which falls under the category of Natural Language Processing (NLP). The paper proposes a novel module to dynamically exploit target semantics from right-to-left translation for enhancing left-to-right translation quality. This involves addressing and reading operations, which are common techniques used in NLP. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves training a model with a regularization term, which is a common technique used in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also involves updating target semantics, which is a common technique used in deep learning and neural networks, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also involves experiments and evaluations, which are common techniques used in neural networks and deep learning, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another likely category. Finally, the paper involves language translation, which is a common application of computer vision and image processing, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) another possible category.
